                            <comment id="131936" author="nameeshambardar@gmail.com" created="Thu, 8 Sep 2016 23:00:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems that the issue is in the class: org.springframework.data.hadoop.fs.FsShellPermissions, in method : changePermissions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here, the targetClz is hardcoded as &quot;org.apache.hadoop.fs.FsShellPermissions$Chmod&quot; when it should actually look at what was passed in op parameter, and load the appropriate class for the operation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
